"Non-bilious means the vomit doesn't have bile, so maybe it's not a lower intestinal obstruction.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.0609,0.10785,0.10864,0.10468,0.098503,0.09353,0.088082,0.082952,0.075869,0.070263,0.058307,0.050422],"unified_progress":[0.05998,0.088057,0.09692,0.1018,0.10227,0.10012,0.095032,0.090003,0.083268,0.07501,0.060244,0.04729]},{"section":8,"text":"But projectile vomiting in a newborn...","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046483,0.089878,0.10209,0.10435,0.10106,0.094734,0.09205,0.086447,0.079631,0.079359,0.066652,0.057263],"unified_progress":[0.076275,0.079077,0.086939,0.09481,0.095717,0.095001,0.093592,0.090995,0.084154,0.083327,0.067547,0.052566]},{"section":9,"text":"Oh, the classic thing that comes to mind is pyloric stenosis.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04953,0.089472,0.10243,0.10611,0.10114,0.092115,0.088312,0.082443,0.076317,0.079978,0.065717,0.066445],"unified_progress":[0.055611,0.071586,0.084971,0.096075,0.096294,0.096419,0.095407,0.091724,0.086954,0.087622,0.073824,0.063512]},{"section":10,"text":"Let me think more.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.33185,0.05377,0.053379,0.06241,0.062727,0.063798,0.059884,0.06685,0.068233,0.063094,0.066084,0.047925],"unified_progress":[0.22021,0.085651,0.064906,0.064568,0.07392,0.072955,0.094809,0.079028,0.075942,0.060779,0.056121,0.051111]},{"section":11,"text":"Pyloric stenosis typically presents around 2-6 weeks of life, which fits here.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.065066,0.13037,0.062793,0.10243,0.10105,0.10031,0.091613,0.083528,0.075128,0.069983,0.06222,0.055504],"unified_progress":[0.073703,0.096107,0.065771,0.097009,0.097638,0.10066,0.093167,0.09172,0.085623,0.079394,0.066428,0.05278]},{"section":12,"text":"The projectile vomiting is a key symptom.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046081,0.088137,0.10137,0.10148,0.098806,0.091911,0.089907,0.084462,0.078902,0.081157,0.070428,0.067358],"unified_progress":[0.049497,0.073223,0.082661,0.092968,0.094436,0.095909,0.094221,0.092861,0.089433,0.090377,0.078751,0.065664]},{"section":13,"text":"The dehydration is also common because they can't hold down enough fluids.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045422,0.084693,0.088299,0.090629,0.093394,0.095697,0.095511,0.092797,0.086857,0.082852,0.076128,0.067721],"unified_progress":[0.049588,0.068931,0.075195,0.079357,0.086972,0.093722,0.093628,0.096489,0.095933,0.095723,0.089781,0.07468]},{"section":14,"text":"Now, the peristaltic wave observed after feeding.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.052594,0.091273,0.091294,0.091049,0.09062,0.092085,0.090698,0.088788,0.088578,0.080808,0.074187,0.068025],"unified_progress":[0.060243,0.075356,0.083005,0.089185,0.09358,0.095201,0.094149,0.092533,0.091956,0.085142,0.075804,0.063846]},{"section":15,"text":"In pyloric stenosis, the stomach can't empty properly because the pylorus is hypertrophic.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039886,0.079515,0.089286,0.096514,0.098708,0.099119,0.098673,0.092344,0.091545,0.080911,0.070986,0.062512],"unified_progress":[0.064328,0.071458,0.087465,0.095487,0.099773,0.1019,0.097415,0.092882,0.090177,0.078229,0.065468,0.055418]},{"section":16,"text":"So after feeding, you might see waves as the stomach tries to push the food through the narrowed pylorus.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046975,0.086041,0.090257,0.095035,0.096153,0.097513,0.096381,0.091219,0.090145,0.079419,0.069624,0.061238],"unified_progress":[0.059726,0.076185,0.09031,0.097472,0.10212,0.10098,0.097091,0.092525,0.089397,0.076247,0.0642,0.053744]},{"section":17,"text":"The movement from left hypochondrium (where the stomach is) to the umbilicus could be the stomach's peristalsis trying to move contents past the blocked pylorus.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047953,0.089269,0.094709,0.099207,0.097042,0.097066,0.094297,0.087643,0.091397,0.076046,0.065941,0.059431],"unified_progress":[0.056632,0.076484,0.09419,0.10399,0.10869,0.10297,0.099078,0.090979,0.089688,0.071257,0.057532,0.048513]},{"section":18,"text":"Wait, another thought: Hirschsprung's disease can cause vomiting too, but that's usually bilious and might have other signs like delayed meconium.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03094,0.066922,0.080819,0.091972,0.099663,0.10222,0.10469,0.10022,0.093557,0.089994,0.077511,0.061488],"unified_progress":[0.034019,0.063171,0.083247,0.093506,0.09955,0.11383,0.10426,0.10116,0.095144,0.090802,0.071067,0.050241]},{"section":19,"text":"This is non-bilious.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02961,0.065503,0.079491,0.087221,0.09226,0.09552,0.099963,0.099962,0.097951,0.094528,0.087312,0.07068],"unified_progress":[0.043353,0.064226,0.07717,0.085517,0.093889,0.096357,0.098407,0.10049,0.098103,0.099622,0.082551,0.060315]},{"section":20,"text":"Also, Hirschsprung's might have a distended abdomen, but the peristaltic wave here is more indicative of upper GI obstruction.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03135,0.068686,0.080282,0.088605,0.092877,0.097118,0.099882,0.097878,0.10068,0.091057,0.082462,0.069128],"unified_progress":[0.036511,0.065314,0.082142,0.092779,0.099289,0.10146,0.10052,0.099416,0.09976,0.09077,0.075768,0.056271]},{"section":21,"text":"Intussusception is another possibility, but that's more common in older infants (like 3-6 months), and the vomiting is usually later in the course.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025246,0.058061,0.071963,0.08377,0.092976,0.099175,0.10562,0.10568,0.10174,0.10008,0.088823,0.066873],"unified_progress":[0.031421,0.058407,0.075315,0.085225,0.095056,0.10368,0.10306,0.1063,0.10292,0.10412,0.081431,0.053069]},{"section":22,"text":"The peristaltic wave description doesn't fit as much.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032255,0.066044,0.075742,0.083156,0.08867,0.093887,0.098743,0.099617,0.10177,0.095428,0.089136,0.075552],"unified_progress":[0.040231,0.063218,0.076482,0.085808,0.093719,0.09675,0.098953,0.10039,0.10072,0.098066,0.083103,0.062554]},{"section":23,"text":"Plus, intussusception would likely have bilious vomiting and a palpable mass, maybe blood in stool.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025313,0.058436,0.071973,0.082803,0.090645,0.096689,0.10392,0.10453,0.10414,0.099759,0.091204,0.07059],"unified_progress":[0.030405,0.05773,0.074781,0.084817,0.094981,0.10032,0.1021,0.10529,0.10448,0.10396,0.084364,0.056771]},{"section":24,"text":"So putting it all together: age, projectile non-bilious vomiting, peristaltic waves after feeding, dehydration.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026851,0.055251,0.067254,0.075846,0.08389,0.089953,0.095016,0.09722,0.10144,0.10276,0.10492,0.099605],"unified_progress":[0.03541,0.052411,0.064928,0.07528,0.084847,0.094964,0.097492,0.10073,0.10353,0.10325,0.10085,0.086308]},{"section":25,"text":"Pyloric stenosis is the most likely.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020015,0.043544,0.05575,0.063995,0.071093,0.076909,0.084498,0.089312,0.098263,0.10424,0.11766,0.17471],"unified_progress":[0.019294,0.033585,0.043478,0.053276,0.059334,0.074602,0.078044,0.093418,0.1049,0.11144,0.14324,0.18539]},{"section":26,"text":"Also, on exam, sometimes you can feel an olive-sized mass in the right upper quadrant, but maybe that's not mentioned here.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029972,0.064112,0.074384,0.081632,0.085954,0.091641,0.095313,0.096543,0.10147,0.096969,0.093425,0.088587],"unified_progress":[0.032926,0.057726,0.072115,0.084898,0.09064,0.093899,0.096924,0.098911,0.10111,0.10009,0.092245,0.078512]},{"section":27,"text":"But the peristaltic waves and the symptoms still point there.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029878,0.062249,0.074019,0.081694,0.087193,0.091416,0.095359,0.095958,0.099851,0.097182,0.094813,0.090387],"unified_progress":[0.036963,0.057733,0.070823,0.081149,0.088623,0.092185,0.095885,0.097868,0.10065,0.098749,0.094222,0.085152]},{"section":28,"text":"I think that's the answer.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028117,0.055185,0.068428,0.076471,0.084117,0.08836,0.092299,0.094964,0.099004,0.098202,0.09915,0.1157],"unified_progress":[0.035679,0.054938,0.065217,0.076781,0.07931,0.082901,0.087676,0.091603,0.095259,0.103,0.10897,0.11867]}]}}